<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1805,2010]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1913,1938]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wingspan 32–35 mm. 
<taxonomicName box="[579,728,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sacculatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[579,728,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">A. sacculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[734,797,1914,1937]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[734,797,1914,1937]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the third new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1098,1165,1914,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[1098,1165,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. It differs externally from its congeners by smaller size (wingspan 32–35 mm), bright colouration forewing, resembling 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parannamita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">A. parannamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Wing pattern formed by golden-green elements on dark-brownish background and especially expressed golden-green subterminal field; hindwing yellowish-grey brown, darker than in 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1382,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parannamita">
<emphasis box="[1203,1382,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">A. parannamita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but paler than in other members of 
<taxonomicName box="[521,588,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[521,588,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group. By male genitalia structure it is close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1364,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai">
<emphasis box="[1247,1364,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">A. owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by narrower and more apically hooked uncus, broader juxta, more rounded cucullus, shorter neck of cucullus and angled lateral extension of sacculus (rounded in 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1022,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai">
<emphasis box="[905,1022,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">A. owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in all species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1279,1346,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis box="[1279,1346,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-species group). Aedeagus with rather short diverticula, medial diverticulum armed by short cutter-like cornutus, different in shape from other species of the group. Female differs by well-formed quadrangular antrum and very short sclerotised ductus bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,425,404,429]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[447,587,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1738,1759]" captionTargetBox="[190,1394,195,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[190,1395,195,1719]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Atrovirensis spp., adults. 1. A. atrovirens, Nepal (after Gyulai et al. 2013); 2. A. annamita, HT, Vietnam (after Gyulai et al. 2013); 3. A. parannamita sp. n., male HT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2930 - 1; 4. A. parannamita sp. n., female PT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2906 - 2; 5. A. pedibus, HT, China, Prov. Hubei (after Gyulai et al. 2013); 6. A. sp. cf. A. parannamita, male, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2907 - 1; 7. A. sinica, HT, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. ZFMK 1624; 8. A. owadai, Prov. Guangdong, HT, China (after Gyulai et al. 2013); 9. A. taiwani, HT, Taiwan (after Gyulai et al. 2013); 10. A. furcatus sp. n., male HT, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2921 - 1; 11. A. furcatus sp. n., female PT, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2919 - 2; 12. A. sp. cf. furcatus, male, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2918 - 1; 13. A. sp. cf. furcatus, female, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2909 - 2; 14. A. sacculatus sp. n., male HT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2910 - 1; 15. A. sacculatus sp. n., male PT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2908 - 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267006/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Figs 14, 15</figureCitation>
). Head and thorax covered with yellowish-green hair-like scales, palps blackish-brown. Ground colour of forewing blackish-brown with yellowish-green dusting; main elements of wing pattern yellowish-green; costal field yellowish-green dusting and with distinct yellowish-green and blackish marks; basal field yellowish-green, basal line distinct; subbasal field filled with yellowish-green, subbasal line slightly waved; medial field blackish-brown with yellow-greenish suffusion, claviform traceable; orbicular and reniform stigmata filled with yellowish-green, rather small, orbicular rounded, both stigmata encircled by dark line; veins suffused with grey; postmedial line waved; subterminal field bright, yellowish-green, with ash-grey veins and light brownish outer suffusion; subterminal line dentate, extended in M1-M2 veins area, pale yellowish-green; terminal field blackish-brown with grey suffusion; terminal line waved, as row black semilunar streaks; cilia yellowishbrown, with black terminal spots between veins. Hindwing yellowish-grey, paler in outer part, with hardly traceable discal spot and in some specimens with diffused terminal band; cilia pale, yellowish-grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,799,824]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[391,473,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 30 – 32" captionStartId="7.[151,263,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1812]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,193,1818]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 30 – 32. Atrovirensis spp., male genitalia. 30. A. furcatus sp. n., HT, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2921 - 1; 31. A. sp. cf. furcatus, China, Prov. Guangdong, genit. prep. HHL- 2918 - 1; 32. A. sacculatus sp. n., HT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2910 - 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267010/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Uncus rather short, thinner than in related species, slightly hooked apically; tegumen with broad peniculus, juxta plate-like, broad; valva narrower than in 
<taxonomicName box="[930,1044,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai">
<emphasis box="[930,1044,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">A. owadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with shorter neck of cucullus and angled lateral extension of sacculus; harpe straight, rather short, smaller than in related species; cucullus larger and more rounded than 
<emphasis box="[368,509,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
in 
<taxonomicName box="[396,509,908,933]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="owadai">A. owadai</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Aedeagus with tubular vesica ended by short ventral diverticulum armed with two small spines and larger medial diverticulum armed with short (about two times shorter than in other species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Atrovirensis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">A. sinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), cutter-like cornutus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,413,1015,1040]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[439,532,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 – 47" captionStartId="16.[151,263,1832,1853]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,564,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,555,1810]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 45 – 47. Atrovirensis spp., female genitalia, habitats. 45. A. sacculatus sp. n., PT, China, Aut. Reg. Xizang, genit. prep. HHL- 2947 - 2; 46. A. yoshimotoi, PT, China, Prov. Guangdong, NSMT-SW- 021 (after Gyulai et al., 2013); 47. A. miraculosus sp. n., PT, China, Prov. Fujian, genit. prep. HHL- 2914 - 2; 48. A. euplexina, China, Prov. Sichuan, genit. prep. GB 12189; 49. Montane monsoon evergreen forest at elevation 2200 m—the habitats of Atrovirensis spp. in Linzhi, Hanmi- Motuo, Aut. Reg. Xizang, China. 50. Montane evergreen mixed forest at elevation 1500 m – the habitat of Atrovirensis spp. in Mt. Nanling (Nanling Nat. Park.), Prov. Guangdong, China." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/267013/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor relatively small, papillae anales constricted apically; antrum quadrangular in shape with antevaginal plate formed by two small scobinate lobes; the ductus bursae very short, sclerotised and bifurcate in joining with corpus bursae; corpus bursae long, narrow, somewhat constricted medially, extended in proximal part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1160,1183]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name indicates for angular shape of sacculus which is the characteristic feature of new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1208,1231,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,1256]" box="[199,1208,1231,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1231,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="216">Distribution.</emphasis>
China (Aut. Reg. Xizang). The species is known only from its type-locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
